Cybersecurity experts say stealing the files is entirely possible. They note Snowden had to go through customs in Hong Kong and then camp out in a Russian airport hotel. He's undoubtedly encountered Chinese and Russian security services. Those countries have cyber capabilities second only to the United States. Mark Weatherford, until recently, the top cyber expert at the Department of Homeland Security, expects the Chinese or the Russians or both have already gotten hold of Snowden's secret files.
